==English==

===Etymology===
From the names of [[w:Albert_Einstein|Albert Einstein]] and [[w:Satyendra_Nath_Bose|Satyendra Nath Bose]], and [[condensate]].

===Noun===
A state of matter in which all the particles (atoms or molecules) as a group are described by a single quantum state.  A Bose-Einstein Condensate is to matter what a laser beam is to light.

''See [[w:Bose-Einstein_condensate|Wikipedia article]] for more information.''

